tures by adapting systems to the current cyber environment  Using the principles of replication  variation  mutation  and differential fitness  competition  observed in nature  the approach discovers more secure computer configurations from previous secure configurations  generations  Fulp is a professor of computer science at Wake Forest University  and head of the network security group there as well  He is the co founder of Great Wall Systems  a network security start up in Winston Salem  N C  Fulp received his doctorate in computer engineering from North Carolina State University  He s a member of the Association for Computing Machinery and a senior member of IEEE  Fulp s appearance at VMI is sponsored by the Department of Computer and Information Science  the Department of Economics and Business  and the Department with English  Rhetoric  and Humanistic Studies  with support from the Jackson Hope Fund   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 